The paper describes the data model and implementation of a new architecture for the National Science Digital Library (NSDL), which is a digital library for science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) education. The architecture is based on the notion of an information network overlay, which is implemented as a graph of digital objects in a Fedora repository. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity). However, given the focus on digital libraries and information management, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely categories.
